workflow.description:
Automate CSV imports into HubSpot without the mess. Powered by n8n. Supercharged by Pollup AI.
## Who‚Äôs this for?
This workflow is perfect for Ops-minded folks in Customer Success, Marketing, and Sales ‚Äì especially if you‚Äôre juggling CSV lists, CRM updates, and team-wide reporting. Whether you're a CS ops lead syncing product usage, or a RevOps manager updating contact records, this will save you hours.

## üß† Why it matters
Manually importing CSVs into HubSpot is a headache:
 ‚ùå Copy-paste errors
 ‚ùå Mismatched fields
 ‚ùå Wasted time formatting every upload
This workflow does the heavy lifting for you:
 ‚úÖ Pulls fields dynamically from your HubSpot instance
 ‚úÖ Preps and maps CSV data in minutes
 ‚úÖ Syncs with Google Sheets to keep your source of truth aligned

## üîÑ What the workflow actually does
1. **Pulls live field names from HubSpot‚Äôs API** (no guesswork)
1. **Indexes and organizes your CSV** for import
1. **Processes & transforms raw data** (optional filters, cleanup, etc.)
1. **Dynamically maps** CSV fields to HubSpot fields
1. **Executes the upload** and logs results


## ‚öôÔ∏è How to get started
**Prerequisites:**
- HubSpot private app token
- Google Sheets API credentials
- Access to an n8n instance (cloud or self-hosted)

**Setup in 3 steps:**
- Import the JSON into your n8n
- Connect your HubSpot and Sheets accounts
- Upload a CSV through the built-in form ‚Äî you‚Äôre live üéâ


## ‚úèÔ∏è Make it yours
- **Add filters** (e.g., remove duplicates, format fields)
- **Add more HubSpot objects** to match your use case
- **Trigger automation** via webhook, schedule, or custom input

Works beautifully with other Pollup AI flows ‚Äì so you can scale CS ops with less stress!


## About Pollup AI
Pollup builds **hands-on automations for B2B communication teams**. This n8n workflow is one of many tools helping lean CS teams deliver high-touch outcomes at scale.

Find out more at pollup.ai

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Execute Workflow node can be used when you want your workflow to treat another workflow as a step in your flow. It allows you to modularize your workflows and have a single source of truth for series of actions you perform often.

data.details: The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
